<paragraph id="C66736D8221FE756FF3F2391C2F815EF" blockId="1.[151,667,1152,1175]" box="[151,667,1152,1175]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
<typeStatus id="1963887A221FE756FF3F2391C0AF15EF" box="[151,204,1152,1175]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">Type</typeStatus>
species: 
<taxonomicName id="01D84D5B221FE756FE852391C2F815EF" authority="Medler, 1992: 24" authorityName="Medler" authorityPageNumber="24" authorityYear="1992" box="[301,667,1152,1175]" class="Insecta" family="Flatidae" genus="Amasha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decepta">
<emphasis id="F4ACEACA221FE756FE852391C1BE15EF" box="[301,477,1152,1175]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">Amasha decepta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="A2494B29221FE756FE4C2391C21515EF" author="Medler" box="[484,630,1152,1175]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" refString="Medler, J. T. (1992) Revision of the tribe Phyllyphantini in the Oriental Region, with descriptions of new genera and new species. Oriental Insects, 26, 1 - 38." type="journal article" year="1992">
Medler, 
<number id="701024FF221FE756FD952391C21515EF" box="[573,630,1152,1175]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="1992.0">1992</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: 
<number id="701024FF221FE756FD282391C2F815EF" box="[640,667,1152,1175]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="24.0">24</number>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C66736D8221FE756FF3F23D4C43C1772" blockId="1.[151,1436,1221,1695]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
Medium-sized planthoppers, overall 
<quantity id="01209B3D221FE756FDE023D4C2A815A7" box="[584,715,1221,1247]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" unit="mm" value="12.0" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="10.0">10–14 mm</quantity>
. Head narrower than pronotum. Vertex wider than long, with dorsal median carina; frons as long as broad approximately, with short median carina and broad U-shaped carina at dorsal margin, lateral margin ridged (
<figureCitation id="5EE32A5D221FE756FD172201C3501452" box="[703,819,1296,1322]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 10. A" captionStartId="3.[151,270,1724,1748]" captionTargetBox="[153,1433,666,1686]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,655,1703]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 10. A. inepta; 7, head and thorax, dorsal view, show transverse intergenal carina (tic); 8, head and thorax, left lateral view; 9, face, show U-shaped carina; 10, tegmen." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/276349/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
Figs. 
<number id="701024FF221FE756FCAB2201C3501452" box="[771,819,1296,1322]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="8.0" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="7.0">7–9</number>
</figureCitation>
); antenna with basal segment very short, concealed, second segment shortly cylindrical, only slightly broader distally than at base. Pronotum slightly longer than head, with disc declivous cephalad, flat, without median carina, postocular eminence ridgelike. Tegmen about twice as long as board, costal membrane as wide as costal cell or a little wider; costal margin weakly convex, apical margin more or less truncate, with one subapical line of crossveins, sutural margin truncate (
<figureCitation id="5EE32A5D221FE756FA9B22B4C5F414C7" box="[1331,1431,1445,1471]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 10. A" captionStartId="3.[151,270,1724,1748]" captionTargetBox="[153,1433,666,1686]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,655,1703]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 10. A. inepta; 7, head and thorax, dorsal view, show transverse intergenal carina (tic); 8, head and thorax, left lateral view; 9, face, show U-shaped carina; 10, tegmen." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/276349/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">Figs. 10</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="5EE32A5D221FE756FF3F22DBC0D4149C" box="[151,183,1482,1508]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,271,1814,1838]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,803,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,789,1793]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 18. Amasha haina sp. nov. 15, head and thorax, dorsal view; 16, head and thorax, left lateral view; 17, face, show U-shaped carina; 18, tegmen." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/276351/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">18</figureCitation>
); three longitudinal veins arising from basal cell (Sc+R, M, Cu), Cu forked, Cu 
<number id="701024FF221FE756FBC222DBC417149C" box="[1130,1140,1482,1508]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="1.0">1</number>
merged with vein M 
<number id="701024FF221FE756FAC622DBC51F149C" box="[1390,1404,1482,1508]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="2.0">2</number>
or not, Y-stem of claval veins very short at apex of clavus. Metatibial lateral spines 
<number id="701024FF221FE756FBE122E1C4381772" box="[1097,1115,1520,1546]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="2.0">2</number>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
